"&#xa0;\nWritten evidence submitted by South West Grid for Learning (SWGfL) [OLS0033]&#xa0;Summary: With over 10 years of pioneering work in online safety and as part of the UK Safer Internet Centre, we are fully aware of emerging technologies and potential risks, the issues children and young people, professionals and parents face, and the gaps that exist in their support; as well as stakeholders and partner organisations working in this field. In the response below we outline strategies we feel would improve online safety in the UK:&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\nSUMMARY OF RESPONSE&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;(Need to write this in bullet points but will do after all have contributed their thoughts)&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\nII. Filtering out extremist material including CAI (Child Abuse Images) and material intended to promote terrorism and/or other acts of violence&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\nIII. Preventing abusive or threatening comments on social media&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\nSeptember 2013\n&#xa0;\n"